    <sharedRules>
        <rule name="Ambush" id="aa0c-ab7e-0415-41cb" hidden="false">
            <description>For each started 500 points of game size, one "Ambush marker" may be set up on the battlefield after all Infiltrators have been deployed, but before the first battle round starts. The marker must be set up 12" away from any enemy unit. Units entering play from reserves with the "Ambush" rule may be set up within 3" of it and be given any kind of order. Additionally, any unit with the "Ambush" rule may be removed from the field when within 3" of an "Ambush marker" and put into reserves. Units that enter reserves in this way automatically arrive during the Reinforcemente phase in the next battle round. They do count towards the limit of how many units may arrive from reserves each round.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Nexus of Devotion" id="c409-d988-a542-4df3" hidden="false">
            <description>During each Reinforcement phase, 1D3 slain models return to the attached unit.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Ringleader" id="3e85-1903-97a7-4ac4" hidden="false">
            <description>You may select up to two units with this ability for a single HQ slot. Each unit may only be taken once.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Sacred Cult Banner" id="4674-c11e-534d-4658" hidden="false">
            <description>The unit gains a bonus of +1 to Leadership and Combat resolutions. As long as the banner bearer is alive, Mission objectives that are held by this unit can not be contested by enemy units. Additionally, all models in the unot gain +1 Attack.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Unquestioning Loyalty" id="60c2-1e7e-0b82-4ad7" hidden="false">
            <description>This model may join any Genestealer Cults creature unit (regardless of their unit type). Additionally, that unit gains the "Bodyguard" ability.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Psyker" id="943c-18af-a1bb-44ed" hidden="false">
            <description>The model can cast 2 powers and deny 2 powers per battle round. It knows Smite and all powers from a chosen discipline.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Living Idol" id="0194-c1ae-43c4-48a4" hidden="false">
            <description>Friendly units within 12" range may use the Patriarch's Leadership value.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Preternatural senses" id="5b1c-4f79-1f8e-4f9f" hidden="false">
            <description>The model gains a 5+ invulnerability save.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Cult Demagogue" id="c72c-1493-5085-4b2f" hidden="false">
            <description>The Primus and its attached unit gain the "Favoured enemy(everything)" ability.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Cult icon" id="c11a-2924-83be-492f" hidden="false">
            <description>During each Reinforcement phase, 1D6 slain models return to the unit.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Monofilament" id="2ef5-cbe9-5de7-4e92" hidden="false">
            <description>If the target enemy unit is in cover and at least one hit has been scored with the weapon, the terrain counts as difficult and dangerous terrain until the end of the next activation of the target unit.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Mindwyrm familiar" id="5cd0-99db-3515-4280" hidden="false">
            <description>The model can re-roll 1 to hit and 1 to wound roll.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="The Chosen One" id="57fa-8777-cfa2-42bb" hidden="false">
            <description>All melee weapons of the Abominant and its attached unit gain the "Deflagrate(5+)" ability.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Alchemicus familiar" id="590d-79e0-6d92-4894" hidden="false">
            <description>Can be used once per battle to grant "Poison(2+)" for all melee weapons of an attached unit until the end of the current battle round.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Genomic enhancement" id="83d4-608c-7426-4afc" hidden="false">
            <description>Once per activation, the model can boost a friendly creature unit within 3" range.
1 - The unit gains +1 Strength. 
2 - The unit gains +1 Toughness. 
3 - The unit gets +1 BS and +1 WS. 
Character models cannot be upgraded. Each unit can only be upgraded once per game.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Proclamation Hailer" id="1a50-0466-a80d-4771" hidden="false">
            <description>Friendly units within 12" automatically pass Leadership tests during the Rally phase.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Scrambler array" id="499c-8814-a2dd-47ac" hidden="false">
            <description>Equipment such as icons or homing beacons do not function within 6" of the model. Additionally, units arriving via deepstrike that land within 12" roll 4D6 instead of 2D6 for scattering.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Voice of New Truths" id="c2a6-599f-b812-42fa" hidden="false">
            <description>Enemy units within 12" suffer a -1 penalty to their Leadership value.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Battlefield Analysis" id="fd46-105b-0c25-45f2" hidden="false">
            <description>Select one enemy unit on the table during each Reinforcement phase. You may re-roll a single hit, wound or armor penetration roll against the target.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Strategic Coordination" id="dcd3-ea62-b017-400b" hidden="false">
            <description>You may re-roll one reserve roll each Reinforcement phase.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Hidden explosives" id="4c92-5f48-4c75-4977" hidden="false">
            <description>Instead of using it like a ranged weapon, the model may set up any Demolition charge it posseses hidden on the table. Place three markers for each Demolition charge face down anywhere on the table that is outside of the enemy deployment zone. Two of these three markers are duds and don't do anything when revealed, while the actual marker causes one automatic hit with the profile of a Demolition charge. Markers are revealed the first time an enemy unit moves within 3" of the marker during its activation.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Transport" id="02d1-9e4a-7267-467e" hidden="false">
            <description>This model has a transport capacity of 10 infantry models.</description>
        </rule>
    </sharedRules>
    <sharedSelectionEntryGroups>
    </sharedSelectionEntryGroups>
